### Compliant Content Model (Amino Foundry Standard)

Every article must follow:
- Purely molecular-mechanism language
- PubMed PMID citations for every claim
- Named scientific team byline
- RUO disclaimer at end of every article
- NO health outcomes, NO human dosing, NO consumer framing

**Good:** "BPC-157 has been examined in rodent models for its interaction with nitric oxide synthase (NOS) pathways and VEGF expression in tissue preparations."

**Bad:** "BPC-157 helps with gut healing and joint recovery."

